# Git and Commit Standards

## Commit Message Format

Use:

```text
<type>(<scope>): <description>
```

Allowed types:
- `feat` new features
- `fix` bug fixes
- `docs` documentation
- `style` formatting or non-functional style changes
- `refactor` internal code restructuring without behavior changes
- `perf` performance improvements
- `test` test updates
- `chore` tooling/dependencies/maintenance
- `ci` CI/CD changes
- `revert` commit reverts

Examples:
- `feat(auth): add OAuth login with Google`
- `fix(ui): resolve button alignment in mobile view`
- `docs(readme): update installation instructions`
- `refactor(api): simplify user data fetching logic`

## Branch Naming

- `feature/<feature-name>`
- `fix/<bug-description>`
- `docs/<documentation-update>`
- `refactor/<component-or-area>`

## Pull Request Expectations

- Use descriptive PR titles.
- Include screenshots for UI changes.
- Link related issues when relevant.
- Request review from the right team members.
